RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 37. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREER CROSSING broke inward, was checked solidly, quickly recovered to share the lead from outside, angled in beside MADELYN ATTACK nearing the quarter pole, was roused leaving the bend, edged ahead with a sixteenth left and began to draw off in the waning yards. MADELYN ATTACK vied for the lead from inside rivals, floated out some when roused leaving the turn, battled gamely but did not have enough left the last sixteenth. ENVEY N ICE settled early, picked up her pace after a quarter mile, threatened along the rail with a furlong to go but leveled off instead. DESTINY'S DREAM contested the pace between rivals for three and a half furlongs then steadily yielded.

ENTRY.NAME: Destiny's Dream
ENTRY.OWNER: Cox John E and Pohl Dennis

ENTRY.NAME: Envey N Ice
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, rail bid, leveled off

ENTRY.NAME: Greer Crossing
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, checked, roused leaving turn, drew clear last 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEORGE'S VISION broke a bit outward, was rated off the early speed from outside, commenced his bid after a half mile, was three wide on the second bend, carried out some into the lane, was all out outside SAFE and narrowly prevailed. SAFE stalked the leader from between rivals, made his bid two wide on the second turn, drifted out some entering the stretch, fought gamely but had to settle for second best. DUCKDEVIL was quickly clear and moved to the inside, showed the way in hand, was challenged from outside on the second bend, gradually wore down the last two furlongs but stayed well clear for third. BRASKA was sent to help prompt the early pace from just off the inside, swung to the outside nearing the quarter pole, came into the stretch widest, had to late bid and was drifting out under left-handed pressure inside the final furlong. OKLAHOMA HEAT showed little in a ground-saving trip.

ENTRY.NAME: Safe
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked between, 2-4 path 2nd turn, dueled, game effort

ENTRY.NAME: Braska
ENTRY.COMMENT: kept close, angled out 2nd turn, drifted out late

ENTRY.NAME: Duckdevil
ENTRY.COMMENT: quickly clear, inside, wore down last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: George's Vision
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated outside, 3 wide bid 2nd turn, dueled, prevailed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 47. Maiden Claiming Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOWN CRIER pinched briefly a few strides from the gate, quickly recovered to dispute the pace, moved clear nearing the end of a quarter mile, lengthened command when allowed on the bend and proved much the best ridden out in the lane. ONE ACE lugged in a bit to bump TOWN CRIER just after the start, was prominent between rivals, did not keep up three wide on the turn but rallied the last eighth and got up for second late. SPAN was settled just off the inside on the backstretch, angled out four wide on the bend, showed a willingness to run late and caught UNCLE O. G. for third in the waning yards. UNCLE O. G. pressed the pace from between horses early, moved clear for second and stayed just off the rail on the turn, was no match for TOWN CRIER when sent down for the drive and gradually wore down deep stretch. WAVE THE GOLD bumped by TOWN CRIER shortly after the break, was sent to be an early factor from inside, advanced on the bend but could not sustain his bid in the lane. LELAND JOHN was sent to prompt the pace from outside but began to fade widest on the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAY STRONG bumped with THACKER FROMM at the break, stalked the early speed from between rivals, took the advantage three wide when asked with two furlongs to go, quickly moved clear and steadily opened up while kept to task in the lane. WINDIGO SPIRIT was sent to help prompt the pace just outside STAY STRONG, came three wide into the stretch, moved clear for second then could only just hold his position late. THACKER FROMM bumped with STAY STRONG at the start, was settled at the back and inside, picked up his pace on the bend, took over third nearing the final sixteenth and also held onto his position in the waning yards. HE'S A FINE MAN pressed the pace from just off the rail on the backstretch, did not keep up on the turn, came into the lane behind WINDIGO SPIRIT, moved outside that one upper stretch and made up minor ground on WINDIGO SPIRIT the final sixteenth. MAGNA PUNCH quickly clear of the others, was overtaken from outside nearing the end of a half mile, came off the rail some upper stretch, drifted out behind WINDIGO SPIRIT with a furlong left, was steadied, moved back toward the inside and continued to gradually yield. AWINBENEATHMYWINGS showed little in a wide trip.

ENTRY.NAME: He's a Fine Man
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3 path turn, angled 4 wide stretch, mild bid

ENTRY.NAME: Magna Punch
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, weakened, drifted out 1/8, steadied

ENTRY.NAME: Stay Strong
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked between, roused 3 wide 1/4, drew away stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Windigo Spirit
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 4 wide, 3 wide 1/4, mild bid, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 7500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEIRUT BEAUTY bumped at the break, was rated between rivals, moved clear when let out three wide on the bend, steadily widened command in the lane and proved much the best ridden out. TEMPLUNA in contention early, angled out to advance on the turn, came into the lane from path five, was no match for BEIRUT BEAUTY but drew away from the rest for the place. SWEET JUSTICE broke inward, bumping BEIRUT BEAUTY, vied for the lead from inside, did not stay with the latter on the bend, came off the rail some entering the stretch and began to flatten out. SUPERTRIX stayed widest of all and failed to have a significant stretch bid. BOBBIE TOO TOO broke alertly, was soon challenged from both sides and began to fade two wide before finishing a half mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Beirut Beauty
ENTRY.COMMENT: let out 3 wide turn, much the best, ridden out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 65. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 23500. FOR (REGISTERED BRED AND/OR FOALED IN ILLINOIS) FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING 10,000 FOR HORSES THAT HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 18 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Claiming Races For $7,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHAALEB'S RANGER urged to stay close early, was two then three wide taking the bend, engaged CANTOO inside the final furlong, edged ahead with a sixteenth left and kept CANTOO at bay. CANTOO prominent toward the outside, lost ground four then five wide through the turn, took the lead upper stretch, was challenged inside the last eighth, fought gamely, lacked the needed late kick but was easily second best. JULYNNE moved to the inside after a quarter mile, had the rail through the bend, took over third inside the final eighth then could only hold her position late. DRAGONFLY KISSES kept close between rivals, came four wide into the stretch and failed to have a significant response. PRIMITY took the lead from inside after travelling a furlong, set a pressure pace, floated out some entering the stretch, was no match for the top pair and slowly wore down between horses inside the last furlong.

ENTRY.NAME: Primity
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, 2-path into stretch, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Ghaaleb's Ranger
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: kept close, 2-3 wide turn, dueled inside 1/8, edged ahead, held

ENTRY.NAME: Cantoo
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5 wide turn, led, dueled, easily 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FANDUEL HORSE RACING RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2022 - 2023. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2022 - 2023 Allowed 6 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZRIK soon had a clear lead and moved to the inside, was challenged with five furlongs to go, roused nearing the end of a half mile, shook free upper stretch, was challenged nearing the final sixteenth, dug in and held on. SIRCORRI pressed the early leader from between horses, came into the lane from path four, steadily closed the gap on the leader and got up in time to share the win with TIZRIK. DEVIL'S RULE hesitated at the break, progressed from outside, lost ground four then five wide through the bend, took over third nearing the last sixteenth and found best stride too late in the waning yards. CHERNYAHOVSKIY broke well but was settled back and well off the inside, lost considerable ground widest through the turn, lost further time angling out to the middle of the track upper stretch, made a strong move the last eighth but came up short. SCARLET CITY engaged TIZRIK from outside after travelling a furlong, floated out some entering the lane, gradually yielded from between rivals and lugged in with seventy yards left. WILLOW RIDGE prominent from inside, began to gradually yield nearing the end of a half mile. FAIRWAY LANE raced in contention just outside WILLOW RIDGE on the backstretch, did not keep up two wide on the bend, lacked a stretch rally, was steadied behind SCARLET CITY in the late going and altered out. TALE OF THE NILE also hesitated at the start, chased while toward the outside, was three wide on the turn, lost ground fanning outside DEVIL'S RULE into the lane and failed to have a late bid.

ENTRY.NAME: Fairway Lane
ENTRY.COMMENT: faded 2 wide turn, steadied, altered out late

ENTRY.NAME: Scarlet City
ENTRY.OWNER: Martinez Ralph and Martin Paul E
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied outside, 2-3 path turn, weakened stretch, lugged in late

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Tizrik
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside speed, roused near 1/4, edged ahead, held on

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Sircorri
ENTRY.OWNER: Bentler Judy and Bush Steven M
